items.raw_desc: Tea Basilur Book Vintage Pyramid 5× 2 g:Do you long to enjoy your cup of delicious tea after a long and tiring day? Then you should not miss Basilur tea. Black tea has been known to mankind since the 16th century. Production begins with the harvesting of Chinese or Assam tea leaves. The next step is called petal wilting, in which the excess water evaporates. The leaves are then rolled. The final step is the oxidation process. The final taste, aroma and colour of the tea depend most on this part of the processing. Oxidation is stopped by rapid heating, e.g. pan-frying, steaming or baking. Basilur tea can be purchased in packs of 10 g.
